The paper proposes a new ensemble approach for anomaly mining, which involves combining results from multiple sources to yield better performance. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of ensemble techniques for classification and clustering. The paper also focuses on event detection in temporal graphs, which suggests a possible sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of consensus methods and evaluation on real-world datasets further supports the likelihood of cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.CR (security and privacy). Finally, the paper employs novel techniques for selecting results to assemble, which could potentially fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
